<subSubSection id="47AF25B76F166266FF257865215C1C1A" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="0F0A763C6F166266FF257865215C1C1A" blockId="23.[151,1436,1128,1333]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
The 
<typeStatus id="D00EC89E6F166266FF78786425BF1DAF" box="[202,250,1129,1153]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">type</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="D00EC89E6F166266FE83786424D81DAF" box="[305,413,1129,1153]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FE70786526321DAE" authority="Hugo, 2010" authorityName="Hugo" authorityYear="2010" box="[450,887,1128,1153]" class="Arachnida" family="Gymnodamaeidae" genus="Gymnodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deswardti">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FE70786527A91DAE" box="[450,748,1128,1152]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">Gymnodamaeus deswardti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6B240BCD6F166266FD41786426321DAE" author="Hugo, E. A." box="[755,887,1128,1153]" firstAuthor="Hugo" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Acarology, 36" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" pagination="199 - 210" part="3" refId="ref14416" refString="Hugo, E. A. (2010) Two new species of Gymnodamaeidae (Acari: Oribatida) from South Africa. International Journal of Acarology, 36 (3), 199 - 210." title="Two new species of Gymnodamaeidae (Acari: Oribatida) from South Africa" type="journal article" year="2010">
Hugo, 
<number id="B97D641B6F166266FC8D786526321DAE" box="[831,887,1128,1152]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were reexamined. The notogaster of this species is convex in lateral view, and some of the caudal notogastral setae are long, twisted and corkscrew-like (
<figureCitation id="978E6AB96F166266FA88788120CA1D8A" box="[1338,1423,1164,1188]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,2007,2030]" captionTargetBox="[254,1353,1405,1965]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[228,1358,1388,1984]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Aleurodamaeus deswardti (Hugo) lateral view with some cerotegument. Scale bar 100 μ m." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217592/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 
<number id="B97D641B6F166266FAC2788120CA1D8A" box="[1392,1423,1164,1188]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). The body is also covered with cerotegument, although not as thickly as 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FC0678BD21781DE6" box="[948,1085,1200,1224]" class="Arachnida" family="Aleurodamaeidae" genus="Aleurodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niedbalai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FC0678BD21781DE6" box="[948,1085,1200,1224]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">A. niedbalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FBF678BD21D81DE6" bold="true" box="[1092,1181,1200,1224]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="26F217556F166266FBF678BD21D81DE6" box="[1092,1181,1200,1224]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
or 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FB7378BD20311DE6" box="[1217,1396,1200,1224]" class="Arachnida" family="Aleurodamaeidae" genus="Aleurodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvadordalii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FB7378BD20311DE6" box="[1217,1396,1200,1224]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">A. salvadordalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FAC878BD258D1DC3" bold="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="26F217556F166266FAC878BD258D1DC3" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. The edges of the famulus-pit on tarsus I (
<figureCitation id="978E6AB96F166266FD0078D926461DC2" box="[690,771,1236,1260]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1733,1756]" captionTargetBox="[223,1370,201,1690]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[210,1376,193,1712]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Legs (trochanter setae not drawn). A. Aleurodamaeus woasi sp. nov. leg I, left, paraxial view, with cerotegumental granules; B. Aleurodamaeus prominens sp. nov. leg I, left, paraxial view, with cerotegumental granules; C. Aleurodamaeus deswardti (Hugo), tarsus of leg I, left, antiaxial view. Scale bars: 50 μ m." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217590/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
Fig. 
<number id="B97D641B6F166266FD5A78D926461DC2" box="[744,771,1236,1260]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
C) stand out as in the other South African 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FB5F78D920D91DC2" box="[1261,1436,1236,1260]" class="Arachnida" family="Aleurodamaeidae" genus="Aleurodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FB5F78D920D91DC2" box="[1261,1436,1236,1260]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">Aleurodamaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FF4E78F5276E1C3E" box="[252,555,1272,1296]" class="Arachnida" family="Gymnodamaeidae" genus="Gymnodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deswardti">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FF4E78F5276E1C3E" box="[252,555,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">Gymnodamaeus deswardti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also displays the other characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FB9778F521911C3E" box="[1061,1236,1272,1296]" class="Arachnida" family="Aleurodamaeidae" genus="Aleurodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FB9778F521911C3E" box="[1061,1236,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">Aleurodamaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is therefore transferred to this genus as 
<taxonomicName id="C8B50DBF6F166266FE78791126CE1C1A" authority="Hugo, 2010" authorityName="Hugo" authorityYear="2010" box="[458,907,1308,1332]" class="Arachnida" family="Aleurodamaeidae" genus="Aleurodamaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deswardti" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FE78791127A81C1A" box="[458,749,1308,1332]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">Aleurodamaeus deswardti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6B240BCD6F166266FD4E791126C61C1A" author="Hugo, E. A." box="[764,899,1308,1332]" firstAuthor="Hugo" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Acarology, 36" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" pagination="199 - 210" part="3" refId="ref14416" refString="Hugo, E. A. (2010) Two new species of Gymnodamaeidae (Acari: Oribatida) from South Africa. International Journal of Acarology, 36 (3), 199 - 210." title="Two new species of Gymnodamaeidae (Acari: Oribatida) from South Africa" type="journal article" year="2010">
Hugo, 
<number id="B97D641B6F166266FCFB791126C61C1A" box="[841,899,1308,1332]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="26F217556F166266FC20791021571C1B" box="[914,1042,1309,1333]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis id="3DC1AA2E6F166266FC20791021571C1B" bold="true" box="[914,1042,1309,1333]" pageId="23" pageNumber="554">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
